g on the ground for ants. It has been recorded breeding between January and March, and breeds in a nest hole 6–14 m (20–46 ft) off the forest floor, in a dead tree. Two eggs are laid. Habitat and threats The Andaman woodpecker is endemic to the Andaman Islands, where it is found in the rain forests of the lowlands. The species is threatened by the loss of habitat, as the human population of the Andaman Islands increases and clears forests for agriculture. Because of this threat, the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) has assessed it as being vulnerable to extinction. References External links Andaman Birdwatching andamanbirdwatching", "shortSummary": "The Andaman woodpecker (Dryocopus hodgei) is a species of bird in the woodpecker family Picidae. It is endemic to the Andaman Islands in In…", "threats": ["栖息地破坏"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e3/Andaman_Woodpecker_%28Dryocopus_hodgei%29_on_a_tree.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-dryocopus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-dryocopus-hodgei", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-dryocopus", "species": "taxonomy-species-dryocopus-hodgei"}, "expandable": true, "x": 18.97, "y": 257.35, "z": -302.15}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-dryocopus", "name": "Dryocopus", "latinName": "Dryocopus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Dryocopus（Dryocopus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联6种鸟类，如北美黑啄木鸟、Black-bodied woodpecker、Lineated woodpecker等6种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 6, "x": 437.71, "y": -409.75, "z": -95.65}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-dryocopus-hodgei", "name": "Andaman woodpecker", "latinName": "Dryocopus hodgei", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Andaman woodpecker（Dryocopus hodgei）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Andaman w